full_text: @jijidraws In Montreal there's A LOT of tattoo artists and competition so people rarely want to get apprentices. So it took me a while to find somewhere and ended up in a walk in shop that wasn't the best. But it was ok to learn, but I left as soon as I could haha.

full_text: @jijidraws I started at 28-29 and was doing illustration for almost 10 years. So I could tell what was good or bad for me and wasn't afraid to speak up cause I had nothing to loose really. If this wasn't working, I had my illustration career.
